metadata.name: FASTER AND FASTER, 1935 by Peter Arkle & TJ Huff & BETTER AND BETTER, 2035 by Peter Arkle & TJ Huff
metadata.description:
Peter Arkle & TJ Huff. On September 3rd Malcolm Campbell breaks the world land speed record at Bonneville Salt Flats, Utah.

He reached 301.129 miles per hour (the first to go over 300 miles per hour)–– in his super streamlined car Blue Bird. Speed was all anyone thought of back then.

Peter Arkle & TJ Huff. Wooden car parts are grown on genetically engineered trees for electric cars. The environment is more important than speed now.
